docs.abstract: Mr. O’Rourke, a former congressman from Texas, seeks to undo the Trump administration’s work at the border with his own immigration plan.
docs.snippet: Mr. O’Rourke, a former congressman from Texas, seeks to undo the Trump administration’s work at the border with his own immigration plan.
docs.lead_paragraph: Leaning on his ties to El Paso, former Representative Beto O’Rourke of Texas has made immigration reform a central pillar of his presidential campaign. His plan seeks to directly undo the work of the Trump administration at the border.

docs.abstract: Representative Tulsi Gabbard served two combat tours in the Middle East, and Mayor Pete Buttigieg was deployed to Afghanistan as with the Navy. They often cite their service.
docs.snippet: Representative Tulsi Gabbard served two combat tours in the Middle East, and Mayor Pete Buttigieg was deployed to Afghanistan as with the Navy. They often cite their service.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the large Democratic primary field of 24 presidential candidates, only Representative Tulsi Gabbard of Hawaii, Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., Representative Seth Moulton of Massachusetts and former Representative Joe Sestak of Pennsylvania are military veterans.

headline.main: Gabbard and Buttigieg on Their Military Service

docs.abstract: Ms. Gillibrand’s strong defense of women’s reproductive rights at a time when they have come under attack has helped her campaign gain steam.
docs.snippet: Ms. Gillibrand’s strong defense of women’s reproductive rights at a time when they have come under attack has helped her campaign gain steam.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Kirsten Gillibrand of New York has struggled to build early momentum in her campaign. But the renewed Republican push to restrict abortion in recent months has offered her an opening to speak out strongly in defense of women’s reproductive rights.

docs.abstract: Mr. Swalwell has sought to stand out in the crowded Democratic field by making addressing gun violence his top priority.
docs.snippet: Mr. Swalwell has sought to stand out in the crowded Democratic field by making addressing gun violence his top priority.
docs.lead_paragraph: Representative Eric Swalwell of California has made gun control the signature issue of his campaign.

docs.abstract: What we learned from the first debate of the 2020 presidential race.
docs.snippet: What we learned from the first debate of the 2020 presidential race.
docs.lead_paragraph: Hi, and welcome to a special post-debate edition of On Politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host.

docs.abstract: Elizabeth Warren delivered on expectations, while Julián Castro made a big splash.
docs.snippet: Elizabeth Warren delivered on expectations, while Julián Castro made a big splash.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren, the only person on the stage Wednesday polling in double digits, was expected to be the star of the first Democratic debate — and for the first half-hour, she was. But by the end, several lower-polling candidates had taken the spotlight: Senators Cory Booker and Amy Klobuchar, and especially Julián Castro.

headline.main: Who Won the First Debate? Experts on the Left and Right Weigh In

docs.lead_paragraph: Every candidate but one on stage Thursday has recently participated in a nationally televised town hall forum, taking tough questions with the cameras rolling. The exception is Mr. Biden.

headline.main: Democratic Debate 2019: What to Watch for on Night 2

docs.abstract: Abortion is anything but a simple issue. But the nuance in how most Americans think about it has all but disappeared from the political conversation, some voters say.
docs.snippet: Abortion is anything but a simple issue. But the nuance in how most Americans think about it has all but disappeared from the political conversation, some voters say.
docs.lead_paragraph: PITTSBURGH — Abortion is an issue that Lynndora Smith-Holmes goes back and forth on. “Six of one, half dozen of the other,” she said the other day as she finished her lunch break.

headline.main: As Passions Flare in Abortion Debate, Many Americans Say ‘It’s Complicated’

docs.abstract: Ms. Klobuchar unveiled a list of well over 100 actions, a majority of which she could pursue with executive power.
docs.snippet: Ms. Klobuchar unveiled a list of well over 100 actions, a majority of which she could pursue with executive power.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota on Tuesday unveiled a list of well over 100 actions she would take in her first 100 days as president if she were elected, a show of policymaking force that is intended to provide a crystal-clear view of the early days of her administration.

headline.main: Amy Klobuchar Outlines Actions She Would Take in First 100 Days if Elected President

docs.abstract: Interviews across Iowa indicate Mr. Biden’s early lead comes from familiarity, nostalgia for the Obama years and strategic calculations about who can win, not just from enthusiasm for his vision.
docs.snippet: Interviews across Iowa indicate Mr. Biden’s early lead comes from familiarity, nostalgia for the Obama years and strategic calculations about who can win, not just from enthusiasm for his vision.
docs.lead_paragraph: OTTUMWA, Iowa — They praise his experience. They are hopeful about his general election prospects. He is often their first choice for president. For now.

headline.main: Joe Biden’s Lead in Iowa Polls Might Be More Fragile Than It Looks
headline.print_headline: Iowans Put Biden in First. (At Least for Now.)
